				<description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img class=&#34;img-fluid &#34;&#xA;            src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-2800x1867.png&#34;&#xA;             srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-576x384.webp 576w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-768x512.webp 768w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-992x661.webp 992w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-1200x800.webp 1200w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-1400x933.webp 1400w, http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/img/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475-2800x1867.webp 2800w&#34; sizes=&#34;100vw&#34; height=&#34;1867&#34; width=&#34;2800&#34; alt=&#34;Featured Image&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction-to-the-controversy&#34; class=&#34;heading &#34;&gt;Introduction to the Controversy&lt;a href=&#34;#introduction-to-the-controversy&#34; aria-labelledby=&#34;introduction-to-the-controversy&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; --&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;svg-inline--fa fas fa-link anchor&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; role=&#34;img&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 576 512&#34;&gt;&lt;use href=&#34;#fas-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In a shocking turn of events, Anthropic, a leading AI research company, was ordered by the White House to revoke SK Telecom&amp;rsquo;s access to its most advanced AI model, Claude Mythos. This decision came just days before Anthropic took its models offline, citing concerns over alleged ties to China. The move has sparked a heated debate about the regulation of AI technology and the potential risks of collaborating with companies from countries with questionable human rights records.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
